translation: Thy Laws are Complete, Thy Words are beyond Comprehension.75.
Thou art the universal Donor, Thou art Omniscient.
Thou art the Enlightener of all, Thou art the Enjoyer of all.76.
Thou art the Life of all, Thou art the Strength of all.
Thou art the Enjoyer of all, Thou art United with all.77.
Thou art worshipped by all, Thou art a mystery for all.
Thou art the Destroyer of all, Thou art the Sustainer of all.78.

gurmukhi: ਅਾਦਿ ਰੂਪ ਅਨਾਦਿ ਮੂਰਤਿ; ਅਜੋਨਿ ਪੁਰਖ ਅਪਾਰ ||
transliteration: Aadh Roop Anaadh Moondat(i) Ajon(i) Purakh Apaar||
translation: Thou art the Supreme Purush, an Eternal Entity in the beginning and free from birth.

gurmukhi: ਸਰਬ ਮਾਨ ਤਿ੍ਰਮਾਨ ਦੇਵ; ਅਭੇਵ ਅਾਦਿ ੳੁਦਾਰ ||
transliteration: Sarab Maan Trimaan Dev Abhev Aadh Udaar||
translation: Worshipped by all and venerated by three gods, Thou art without difference and art Generous from the very beginning.

gurmukhi: ਸਰਬ ਪਾਲਕ ਸਰਬ ਘਾਲਕ; ਸਰਬ ਕੋ ਪੁਨਿ ਕਾਲ ||
transliteration: Sarab Paalak Sarab Dhaalak Sarab Ko Poun(i) Kaal||
translation: Thou art the Creator Sustainer, Inspirer and Destroyer of all.

gurmukhi: ਜੱਤ੍ਰ ਤੱਤ੍ਰ ਬਿਰਾਜਹੀ; ਅਵਧੂਤ ਰੂਪ ਰਿਸਾਲ ||੭੯||
transliteration: Jattra Tattra Biraaj-hoo Avdhoot Roop Rasaal||79||
translation: Thou art present everywhere like an ascetic with a Generous disposition.79.

gurmukhi: ਨਾਮ ਠਾਮ ਨ ਜਾਤ ਜਾਕਰ; ਰੂਪ ਰੰਗ ਨ ਰੇਖ ||
transliteration: Naam Thaam Na Jaat(i) Jaakar Roop Ran Na Rekh||
translation: Thou art Nameless, Placeless, Casteless, Formless, Colourless and Lineless.

gurmukhi: ਅਾਦਿ ਪੁਰਖ ੳੁਦਾਰ ਮੂਰਤਿ; ਅਜੋਨਿ ਅਾਦਿ ਅਸੇਖ ||
transliteration: Aadh Purakh Udaar Moondat(i) Ajon(i) Aadh Asekh||
translation: Thou, the Primal Purusha, art Unborn, Generous Entity and Perfect from the very beginning.
